body:
Agreed on the problem statement. Rules that report on an entire class, function, or other large area/block are rather disruptive. They drown out other complaints and are visually intimidating at first. 

However, I'm not sure what the best path forward is. Underlining just the function name is a pretty small surface area, but isn't actually code from the reported issue! Maybe having the report range include the `function` keyword & any other modifier(s) such as `export`, as well as the parameter, would be a good compromise?

```ts
export function getToggleOptions({
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  one,
~~~~~~
  two,
~~~~~~
}) {
~~~~
  // ...
  // ...
  // ...
}
```
